-- Danish Oct consumer confidence index rises to 8.2 points 
-- By Annabella Nielsen
-- Thu Oct 23, 2014 03:07AM EDT
-- None



COPENHAGEN, Oct 23 (Reuters) - Denmark's consumer confidence index rose to 8.2 points in October from 7.1 points in September, the statistics office said on Thursday.

Oct 2014Sep 2014   Full-year 2013  Consumer confidence8.2 7.1  1.4   The monthly survey asks a cross section of Denmark's population its views on current personal and national economic trends, along with consumer intentions for the coming months.